Prediksi Kanker Payudara Jinak vs Ganas Berdasarkan Karakteristik Sel (Diagnostic Dataset)#

Notebook ini menggunakan dataset Breast Cancer Wisconsin (Diagnostic) dari UCI Machine Learning Repository.

1. Data Understanding#

Sumber Dataset#

  • UCI ML Repository - Breast Cancer Wisconsin (Diagnostic)

Penjelasan Fitur dan Variabel#

Dataset ini berisi hasil diagnosis kanker payudara berdasarkan fitur-fitur yang diekstrak dari gambar digital aspirasi jarum halus (FNA) massa payudara.

  • ID: Nomor identifikasi pasien

  • Diagnosis: Target (M = malignant/ganas, B = benign/jinak)

  • 30 fitur numerik: radius, texture, perimeter, area, smoothness, compactness, concavity, concave points, symmetry, fractal dimension (masing-masing ada mean, se, worst)

import pandas as pd
import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import seaborn as sns
from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split
from sklearn.preprocessing import StandardScaler
from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier
from sklearn.naive_bayes import GaussianNB
from sklearn.neighbors import KNeighborsClassifier
from sklearn.metrics import classification_report, accuracy_score, confusion_matrix
import joblib

# Download dataset dari UCI
url = 'https://archive.ics.uci.edu/ml/machine-learning-databases/breast-cancer-wisconsin/wdbc.data'
columns = ['ID', 'Diagnosis',
           'radius_mean', 'texture_mean', 'perimeter_mean', 'area_mean', 'smoothness_mean', 'compactness_mean', 'concavity_mean', 'concave points_mean', 'symmetry_mean', 'fractal_dimension_mean',
           'radius_se', 'texture_se', 'perimeter_se', 'area_se', 'smoothness_se', 'compactness_se', 'concavity_se', 'concave points_se', 'symmetry_se', 'fractal_dimension_se',
           'radius_worst', 'texture_worst', 'perimeter_worst', 'area_worst', 'smoothness_worst', 'compactness_worst', 'concavity_worst', 'concave points_worst', 'symmetry_worst', 'fractal_dimension_worst']
data = pd.read_csv(url, header=None, names=columns)

2. Preprocessing Data#

  • Drop kolom ID

  • Transformasi label (M=1, B=0)

  • Standarisasi fitur

  • Split data train/test (80:20)

# Drop kolom ID
data = data.drop('ID', axis=1)
# Transformasi label
data['Diagnosis'] = data['Diagnosis'].map({'M': 1, 'B': 0})
# Split fitur dan label
X = data.drop('Diagnosis', axis=1)
y = data['Diagnosis']
# Standarisasi
scaler = StandardScaler()
X_scaled = scaler.fit_transform(X)
# Split data
X_train, X_test, y_train, y_test = train_test_split(X_scaled, y, test_size=0.2, random_state=42, stratify=y)
print('Train:', X_train.shape, 'Test:', X_test.shape)

Train: (455, 30) Test: (114, 30)

# Visualisasi distribusi label pada train/test
fig, ax = plt.subplots(1,2, figsize=(10,4))
sns.countplot(x=y_train, ax=ax[0])
ax[0].set_title('Train Label')
sns.countplot(x=y_test, ax=ax[1])
ax[1].set_title('Test Label')
plt.show()

3. Modelling#

  • Decision Tree

  • Gaussian Naive Bayes

  • K-Nearest Neighbor (KNN)

# Decision Tree
dt = DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=42)
dt.fit(X_train, y_train)
y_pred_dt = dt.predict(X_test)
acc_dt = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_dt)
print('Decision Tree Accuracy:', acc_dt)

Decision Tree Accuracy: 0.9298245614035088

# Gaussian Naive Bayes
gnb = GaussianNB()
gnb.fit(X_train, y_train)
y_pred_gnb = gnb.predict(X_test)
acc_gnb = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_gnb)
print('GaussianNB Accuracy:', acc_gnb)

GaussianNB Accuracy: 0.9210526315789473

# K-Nearest Neighbor
knn = KNeighborsClassifier(n_neighbors=5)
knn.fit(X_train, y_train)
y_pred_knn = knn.predict(X_test)
acc_knn = accuracy_score(y_test, y_pred_knn)
print('KNN Accuracy:', acc_knn)

KNN Accuracy: 0.956140350877193

4. Evaluasi Model#

  • Classification report dan confusion matrix untuk masing-masing model

# Decision Tree
print('Decision Tree Classification Report:')
print(classification_report(y_test, y_pred_dt))
cm_dt = confusion_matrix(y_test, y_pred_dt)
sns.heatmap(cm_dt, annot=True, fmt='d', cmap='YlGnBu')
plt.title('Confusion Matrix - Decision Tree')
plt.xlabel('Predicted')
plt.ylabel('Actual')
plt.show()

  • Simpan model terbaik (misal KNN) dan scaler

joblib.dump(knn, 'model_knn_diagnostic.pkl')
